text.tspan: Together, Lord, our voice we raise
We seek God’s heart and stand in death,
Pass through the cross in prayer to God
By life and light we’re energized,
At every time renewed and fresh,
Our prayers will judge and end this age
As we the Kingdom’s warfare wage.
Such prayers are bowls with Christ therein,
Added to bring God’s Kingdom in.
The Devil will be cast to earth
Before the throne a loud voice heard,
With Satan driven from the throne,
O Lord, our corporate prayer we raise
To overcome, to end this age.
Your Kingdom come, Your will be done
On earth in us, as at the throne.
’Tis ours to pray, God’s burden own,
Till answers pour out from the throne.
